reviews.review_text: jerry jerry's voice is sounding good
An 86 Surprise I'll second a four star for this show! Nice Aiko opener and great Mississippi/Franklin's.  My favorite is Cape Cod Fall 79, but this is pretty solid!
Hey Now! This show rocks, plain and simple.  Recording is impeccable and goes unnoticed, as if you're there.
Crazy show, with some total chaos happening in the 2nd set.
comment, not review Babe in the woods at this one. Crazy times! Thought the Dead were destroying there equipment after an epic China Doll !?! WHAT!! Good stuff

This show was in New hampshire Twas true, we didn't rue.Just in time plus me and my uncle went to Gergs house in NH and guess what, the Kaiser was there, in this part of NH called Oakland, that our airplane happened to land. How was Just out of prison supposed to know that Nashua isn't in Oakland, by the time we figured it out ,as we were only 17 and 16 or so respectively, we woke up in Oakland. The poor boy was on the line and momma said you ain't in New Hampshire, and I said well ya know That w ould be something.

Into Deal and back for a show kind of rattled as I did actually have a conscience. That was one of the nicest hotels in NH. We had the Maraantz and had a bad tape of this thing for a while, nice to hear it, and so what if you don't think this show is in NH, we insist it is, and we'll challenge you to prove otherwise, and don't call Ian or Brian B., there the ones who "Busted us". All that and we did the same for 8/30/85 but that wasn't in Texas and no one found out....as of now I couldn't figure out which one was jerry at the 12/27/15 show. But it was in SF, I think.then I started collage in California and majored in Parking Lot studies. The degree was in Environmental Art, such as the configuration f the long beach arena and such, with carl Hertel, at Pitzer College, regardless, NH sucks don't go there and the Kaiser is no longer there anyways that was just for 2 days in 86.

On this Day Very nice show and superb soundboard.  Ah, Saturday night at HJK, a 20 minute walk from our friends place the other side of Lake Merritt.  Home sweet home, we were all so lucky to see them there!
